EucaTest version 0.01
=====================

EucaTest is an attempt to leverage existing test code to make test writing faster.

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries which can be installed using CPAN:

  IO::Pty
  Net:OpenSSH

CREATING YOUR LOCAL TEST CREATION ENVIRONMENT

1) Install Eclipse
2) Install the EPIC Perl Plugin
	- Select Help > Software Updates... in Eclipse, add the update site http://e-p-i-c.sf.net/updates/testing and follow the on-screen instructions.
	- Setup the following options in Preferences->Perl EPIC->Source Formatter
		- Cuddle else [checked]
		- Perltidy options: [-l=999]
3) Create test-area
	 mkdir test-area;
	 cd test-area
	 mkdir input; mkdir stage; mkdir share;
	 cd share; mkdir perl_lib; 
	 git clone https://viglesiasce@bitbucket.org/viglesiasce/eucatest.git
	 mv eucatest EucaTest
4) Download the run_instance.pl script from https://bitbucket.org/viglesiasce/eucatest/downloads/run_instance.pl
5) Copy that file to test-area/stage and make it executable with 'chmod +x run_instance.pl'
6) Download the sample_input.conf file from https://bitbucket.org/viglesiasce/eucatest/downloads/sample_input.conf and place it in test-area/input 
7) Run that file to ensure the environment has been setup properly
8) If you are updating the EucaTest.pm library found in test-area/share/perl_lib/EucaTest/lib/EucaTest.pm
	- Ensure that before you commit you go to Source->Format in the Menu Bar to maintain style

SAMPLE FIRST SCRIPT

#!/usr/bin/perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use Cwd qw(abs_path);
use lib abs_path("../share/perl_lib/EucaTest/lib");
use EucaTest;

### Pass in password if keys have not been exchanged between the tester and DUT
my $clc_connection = EucaTest->new( {password =>"foobar" });

### Create a user using euare commands
$clc_connection->euare_create_user("user1", "eucalytpus");

### Get credentials for the user
$clc_connection->get_cred("eucalyptus", "user1","user_cred");

### The fail count gets incremented everytime the fail function is called
if( $clc_connection->get_fail_count() > 0){
	exit(1);
}else{
	exit(0);	
}


